    "Body": " Requisition ID: 75356 Join the Global Community of Scotiabankers to help customers become better off. Director of Communications & Strategic Initiatives will lead and oversee the Global Business Technology Communications, Culture & Development function, ensuring business strategies, plans and initiatives are executed / delivered in compliance with governing regulations, internal policies and procedures. The Role In this role you will be responsible for developing and implementing a compelling narrative, ongoing communications strategies, and impactful communications plans in Canada and the Pacific Alliance countries (Mexico, Peru, Chile and Colombia). You will lead complex cross-functional initiatives and work closely with a diverse range of stakeholders to increase connection to Bank, business, IT&S and Tech strategies and priorities. You will need to provide ongoing strategic communication support to the Global Chief Information Officer and other senior executives within Global Business Technology in the implementation of their business strategies and initiatives. This includes a lead role in the creative development, project management and oversight of multiple executive and corporate communications initiatives of significant complexity. Is this role right for you? You want to Lead and design creative, robust, multimedia, strategic communications plan to build an integrated communications culture and development function for Scotiabank\u2019s Global Business Technology group Participate in executive leadership forums \u2013 both operational and strategic in nature \u2013 and align communications and culture strategies with business goals; partner with key stakeholders to progress Scotiabank\u2019s technology transformation priorities Communicate the Global Business Technology Transformation strategy and its ongoing execution to key audiences. Enhance the profile of leaders and communicate the Bank\u2019s priorities and partnerships to enhance the reputation of the Bank and position the Bank as a global digital banking leader in not only digital banking, but customer-driven software development and the overall digital talent market Develop and execute proactive external communication strategy and message development, coaching and advising leaders, writing, production, and distribution of messages. Ensure appropriate coordination and alignment to connect Global Business Technology initiatives with the broader communications ecosystem of the Bank, internally and externally Facilitate a culture of open and honest communication by actively participating in and contributing to the generation of new ideas and approaches and build effective working relationships with key partners within and beyond Digital Banking, Global Communication, Finance, Operations, Compliance, HR, Marketing, and others. Do you have the skills that will enable you to succeed in this role? You\u2019re a communications expert who can work independently and have solid understanding of the current and prospective media and social media environment in which the Bank operates and key emerging issues of strategic importance to the Bank and its business objectives You\u2019re current on communication trends, best practices in strategy development and ability to adapt these to the strategic planning process You have both an excellent understanding of and a passion for digital and technology industry trends (Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning, Blockchain, Cybersecurity, etc.) as well as the FinTech space in particular You have 8+ years of experience in digital/technology communications, corporate communications, marketing communications and/or public relations You have significant experience driving communications strategies across traditional and emerging communication platforms including social media You have Strong leadership, presentation, writing skills and you\u2019re willing to roll up your sleeves and get the work done University Degree / post-graduate education in Communication/Public Relations. Accredited Business Communicators, IABC or CPRS, Canadian Public Relations Society desired What's in it for you? We have an inclusive and collaborative working environment that encourages creativity, curiosity, and celebrates success! We provide you with the tools and technology needed to create beautiful customer experiences You'll get to work with and learn from diverse industry leaders, who have hailed from top technology companies around the world Dress codes don't apply here, being comfortable does Onsite cafeteria Easily accessible by public transit Opportunity to drive results in a fast paced, challenging and dynamic business environment in this 12 Months Contract position Location(s): Canada : Ontario : Toronto As Canada's International Bank, we are a diverse and global team. We speak more than 100 languages with backgrounds from more than 120 countries. Our employees are committed to a superior customer experience and use the Bank\u2019s six guiding sales practice principles to ensure they act with honesty and integrity. At Scotiabank, we value the unique skills and experiences each individual brings to the Bank, and are committed to creating and maintaining an inclusive and accessible environment for everyone. If you require accommodation (including, but not limited to, an accessible interview site, alternate format documents, ASL Interpreter, or Assistive Technology) during the recruitment and selection process, please let our Recruitment team know. If you require technical assistance, please . Candidates must apply directly online to be considered for this role. We thank all applicants for their interest in a career at Scotiabank; however, only those candidates who are selected for an interview will be contacted. ", 
